{
  "text": "The data presented in this article include the experimental solubility of Phenanthrene (Y) at different temperatures and pressures in carbon dioxide under supercritical conditions [CITATION_1] . Table 1 . The physical properties of the solvent; molecular weight (M), critical pressure (P c ), critical temperature (T c ), acentric factor (\u03c9), Table 2 . The properties of the solute; molecular weight (M), A and B (variables in Redlich-Kwong equation of state) and molar volume (V sol ), they were obtained from the literature [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The solubility values calculated using the modified Redlich-Kwong equation of state with adjustable parameters (\u03b1 and \u03b2) are shown in Table 3 .",
